=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_BinaryOpUGen_ex5 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark gritty sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 60 Hz, featuring slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 60.1513
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.6685
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9899
  pitch_clarity: 0.3962
  inharmonicity: 0.1459
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -3.3180
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: BinaryOpUGen Example 5
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/BinaryOpUGen.html
// Tags: BinaryOpUGen, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 5 ---
(
{
    var a = SinOsc.ar(1).round(0.1);
    var b = SinOsc.ar(1.2).round(0.1);
    BinaryOpUGen('==', a, b) * 0.1
}.play;
)
